  "texts": [
    "If {x ∈ S ⊥ | R i ⊥ (x) ⊆ ↓y} = ⊥, then (4.1)holds, so suppose it is not ⊥.",
    "Then to establish (4.1), suppose forreductio that {x ∈ S ⊥ | R i ⊥ (x) ⊆ ↓y}R i ⊥ z but z ̸ ⊑ ⊥ y.",
    "Then z ̸ = ⊥, so {x ∈ S ⊥ | R i ⊥ (x) ⊆ ↓y}R i z, and z ∧ y * ̸ = ⊥, so z ∧ y * ⊑ z.",
    "Let z ′ = z ∧ y *.",
    "Then by R⇒win for R i, there is an x ′ ⊑ {x ∈ S | R i (x) ⊆ ↓y} such that (i) ∀x ′′ ⊑ x ′ ∃z ′′ ≬ z ′: x ′′ R i z ′′."
